I-Based Fault Detection in Transmission Lines

Overview
This project uses Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning techniques to detect faults in transmission lines. The system continuously monitors electrical parameters like voltage and current to identify abnormal conditions quickly and accurately. It helps improve the reliability and safety of power transmission systems.

Problem Statement
Traditional fault detection methods in transmission lines are slow and require manual monitoring. Delays in fault identification can lead to power loss, equipment damage, and safety issues. An intelligent automated system is needed for faster and more accurate fault detection.

Proposed Solution
The proposed system uses AI/ML algorithms to analyze transmission line data in real time. The system detects faults automatically, classifies the fault type, and alerts the user immediately. This reduces response time and improves overall power system efficiency.

Features:
   Real-time fault detection
   AI/ML-based analysis
   Voltage and current monitoring
   Automatic fault alerts
   Fault location identification
   Improved detection accuracy
   Continuous monitoring system
   User-friendly interface
   Increased system reliability
System Architecture:
  Sensors collect voltage and current data
  Data is sent to the processing unit
  AI/ML model analyzes the data
  Fault is detected and classified
  Alert is generated to the user/dashboard
Components:
Voltage Sensor
Current Sensor
Microcontroller / Raspberry Pi
AI/ML Model
Transmission Line Dataset
Display or Monitoring Dashboard
Power Supply Unit

Working Principle:
The sensors continuously monitor transmission line parameters. The collected data is processed using an AI model trained to identify abnormal conditions. When a fault occurs, the system detects it instantly, classifies the type of fault, and sends an alert for quick action.

Current Status:
Basic system design completed
AI model under development/testing
Sensor integration is in progress
Real-time monitoring module implemented
Fault detection accuracy being improved
Future Improvements:
  IoT-based remote monitoring
   Cloud data storage integration
   Mobile app notifications
   More accurate fault localization
   Faster AI prediction models
   Energy-efficient hardware implementation
